Which of the following regions is the main part of the neuron that contains neurotransmitter receptors (i.e. recieves incoming messages)? <image 1>

A. A
B. B
C. C
D. D
E. E
F. F

The main part of the neuron that contains neurotransmitter receptors is labeled as **C**. This is the cell body (A) where the neuron's axon (D) branches out. The axon contains the neurotransmitter receptors that are responsible for receiving incoming messages from other neurons. Therefore, the correct answer is:

C. C
